ENTRY       EC 3.4.24.75                Enzyme
NAME        lysostaphin;
            glycyl-glycine endopeptidase
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on peptide bonds (peptidases);
            Metalloendopeptidases
REACTION    Hydrolysis of the -Gly!Gly- bond in the pentaglycine inter-peptide link joining staphylococcal cell wall peptidoglycans
COMMENT     A zinc-dependent, 25-kDa endopeptidase from Staphylococcus simulans. Lyses cells of S. aureus, in particular, by its action on the cross-bridges of the cell wall. Type example of peptidase family M23.
